Share with:
Key Account Manager Job (Telecommunications), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Marketing
Industry:
Telecommunications
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Rp. 30.000.000
Created:
05 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the largest-independent owners and operators of towers for wireless operators in Indonesia. Its core business is leasing space at its multi-tenant towers for all major wireless operators in Indonesia under long-term lease agreements. Our client is seeking a sales and marketing professional for the job of Key Account Manager, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
Key job responsibilities will include:
Identify potential new business opportunities
Agenda of the corporate plan with other telecom companies, both in terms of business and technical
Negotiate business and forge cooperation with telecommunications operators
Resolve domestic and international co-operation agreements
Resolve issues that occur regarding interconnection and leased-lines
Requirements:
Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's degree, any field.
At least 8 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position
Healthy and willing to travel around Indonesia
Highly skilled in salesmanship and leadership
Fluent in English
Good report writing skills
Excellent strategic business and analytical skills
Good presentation, communication and negotiation skills
Able to deliver timely and quality results under limited supervision
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.